not_not_lem
-----------

-- Proof that ~~(a \/ ~a) is intuitionistically valid
l1: $ ┬Č (a ÔłĘ ┬Č a) ÔŐó ┬Č (a ÔłĘ ┬Č a) $ by ax []
-- Derive ~a from ~(a \/ ~a)
l2: $ a ÔŐó a $ by ax []
l3: $ _ctx ÔŐó a ÔłĘ ┬Č a $ by or_intro_l [l2]
l4: $ _wff $ by not_elim [l1, l3]
l5: $ _wff $ by not_intro [l4]
-- Now a \/ ~a from ~a
l6: $ _ctx ÔŐó a ÔłĘ ┬Č a $ by or_intro_r [l5]
-- Contradiction
l7: $ _wff $ by not_elim [l1, l6]
-- Conclude ~~(a \/ ~a)
l8: $ _ ÔŐó ┬Č ┬Č (a ÔłĘ ┬Č a) $ by not_intro [l7]

